# Chat Visible Area Definition

- Unless the user explicitly says otherwise, 「可视区域」 in chat positioning, slot height, scroll alignment, and "go to bottom" threshold work means:
  - the area between the chat top bar and bottom bar;
  - minus visible shortcut entry height;
  - minus collapsed pinned todo card height.
- If shortcut entries or the pinned todo card do not exist in the current context, do not subtract that missing height.
- Do not use the raw window height or raw scroll container height as the final visible area when these occupied regions are present.
- New conversation slot height is always fixed to `max(200px, round(可视区域 * 0.8))` across the system.
- This 80% rule is a global default from page load, not a demo-node-triggered mode or an adjustable setting.
